</ref>\n|rev8 = ''[[Now (newspaper)|Now]]''\n|rev8score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>[http://www.nowtoronto.com/music/story.cfm?content=180034 Now review]</ref>\n|rev9 = ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]''\n|rev9score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=metacritic/>\n|rev10 = ''[[Uncut (magazine)|Uncut]]''\n|rev10score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=metacritic/>\n|rev11 = ''[[The Washington Post]]''\n|rev11score = (favorable)<ref>[https://articles.washingtonpost.com/2011-06-30/news/35234319_1_album-review-kd-siss-boom-bang The Washington Post review]</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Sing It Loud''''' is the thirteenth [[studio album]] by [[k.d. lang]] and was released on {{Start date|2011|4|1}}. It is her first collection of original material since 2008's ''[[Watershed (k.d. lang album)|Watershed]]''.\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs written by [[k.d. lang]] and [[Joe Pisapia]] unless otherwise noted.\n#\"I Confess\" (lang, Daniel Clarke, Joshua Grange) \u2013 4:25\n#\"A Sleep with No Dreaming\" \u2013 3:31\n#\"The Water's Edge\" \u2013 3:53\n#\"Perfect Word\" \u2013 4:41\n#\"Sugar Buzz\" \u2013 5:14\n#\"Sing It Loud\" (Pisapia) \u2013 5:25\n#\"Inglewood\" \u2013 3:30\n#\"Habit of Mind\" (lang, Clarke, Grange) \u2013 4:13\n#\"[[Heaven (Talking Heads song)|Heaven]]\" ([[David Byrne]], [[Jerry Harrison]]) \u2013 4:10\n#\"Sorrow Nevermore\" (lang, Clarke, Grange) \u2013 3:33\n\n14-track version exclusive to kdlang.com includes:\n\n<ol start=\"11\">\n<li>\"[[Reminiscing]]\" ([[Graeham Goble]]) \u2013 3:45\n<li>\"I Am the Winner\"  \u2013 2:26 \n<li>\"Hollywood Kids\" \u2013 3:53\n<li>\"Hungry Bird\" \u2013 4:42\n</ol>\n\n==Release history==\n{|class=wikitable\n!Region\n!Date\n!Label\n|-\n|[[Australia]]\n|April 1, 2011\n|WEA\n|-\n|[[United States]]\n|April 11, 2011\n|[[Nonesuch Records]]\n|-\n|[[Netherlands]]\n|April 15, 2011\n|[[Nonesuch Records]] / [[Warner Music]]\n|-\n|[[United Kingdom]]\n|April 18, 2011\n|[[Nonesuch Records]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable